# Auto-Update Table of Contents

Always update the table of contents in [README.md](mdc:README.md) when adding, removing, or modifying categories or sections.

## Table of Contents Rules

1. **Keep TOC synchronized** - The table of contents must always reflect the actual content structure
2. **Use consistent formatting** - All TOC entries should follow the same format and indentation
3. **Update links** - Ensure all TOC links point to the correct section headers
4. **Maintain order** - Keep the TOC in the same order as the content appears in the file

## TOC Format

```markdown
## üìã Table of Contents

- [Section Name](#section-name)
- [Another Section](#another-section)
  - [Subsection](#subsection)
```

## When to Update TOC

- Adding new categories or sections
- Removing categories or sections  
- Renaming categories or sections
- Reordering content
- Adding subsections within categories

## Example

If you add a new "Hardware" section, immediately update the TOC:

```markdown
